a. 2147483647
b. -2147483648;
binary representation in memory of a is 0111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111;
by adding 1, we perform binary addition which results in 1000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000, which is
interpreted as -2147483648
c. -2147483645
d. 2147483647; integer overflow;
-2 is 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1110 in two's complement;
-2147483647 is 1000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0001
after performing binary addition on them, we get 1 0111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111;
the most significant bit is lost due to overflow and thus we get 2147483647
e. -2; integer overflow;
-2 * 2147483647 is really 2147483647 + 2147483647, which in binary is
0111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 +
0111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 =
1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1110
which is -2
d. -4 because 2 * a is -2